    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Any increase needs to be tested and demonstrated to be performant on all Status platforms (as this limit needs to be exactly the same on all platform to ensure compatibility between problems).  Specifically:\r\n\r\n- There used to be an ad-hoc group chat encryption performance issue on the Windows version of Status Desktop.  Before increasing the limit, we need to make sure we won't run into an issue again.\r\n\r\n- We would also need to benchmark ad-hoc group chat scaling in Status Web.  Our web platform has a different stack from Status Mobile and Desktop (no status-go, everything in typescript on top of waku-js) so it might have different perf. issues from Status Mobile and Desktop.  ",
